        "text": "<@U02E4DAQGSZ> The obvious issue with exponential curves is that they cannot go on forever in a finite universe. To make it worse, our resource universe is just one planet plus the sunlight that hits it. I still have some hope that our species will recognize this basic physics fact before being hit by it in the form of a massive crash.",
