                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Show, don't tell "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "emoji",
                                "name": "slightly_smiling_face",
                                "unicode": "1f642"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " If LLMs make a new tooling layer possible, let's see it. I think you have enough ideas, stop bouncing them around. Show one compiler or library or curriculum every week for this diagrammatic medium.\n\nI think you'll find that text has a lot more than fifty years of momentum. More like three thousand years. And it consists not of solutions but of evaluation. We spent years trying out alternatives before we settled on the current state. I don't think AI speeds up evaluation, even if we accept all the current hype. So you might be able to speed up three thousand years to a thousand at best."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
