        "client_msg_id": "6d27f1a7-17b4-46c3-8e49-8da86ee78ffe",
        "text": "Drawings have an even longer history than text. But drawings conveying _precise_ information are very recent. I don't know about diagrams, but the person credited for having invented infographics is William Playfair, late 18th century. At that time, semi-formal textual notations were already in general use in science, and tables well established in accounting.\n\n<https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/William_Playfair>",
